ENTRY            F0543   20251214   20260305   20260305       F105
SUBENT        F0543001   20251214   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                 10         23
TITLE      Gamma-decay from two-quasiparticle states populated
           in the 161,163Dy(d,t) reactions
AUTHOR     (T.Ramsoy,J.Rekstad,M.Guttormsen,A.Henriquez,
           F.Ingebretsen,T.Rodland,T.F.Thorsteinsen,G.Lovhoiden)
INSTITUTE  (2NOROSL,2NORBGN)
REFERENCE  (J,NP/A,438,301,1985)
FACILITY   (CYCLO,2NOROSL)
METHOD     (EDE)
DETECTOR   (TELES,NAICR,GELI) The experimental set-up consisted
           of four particle telescopes, two 12.7 cm x 12.7 cm
           NaI(Tl) and one Ge(Li) counter. The gamma-ray energy
           resolution of the NaI counters was 7%. The Ge(Li)
           counter had an efficiency of 20% with a resolution of
           2.2 keV at 1.3 MeV. The telescopes were placed at
           50 degree with respect to the beam direction and had
           front and end Si counters with thicknesses of 150 um
           and 3000 um, respectively.
COMMENT    The authors gave cross sections relative to the elastic
           deuteron scattering.
STATUS     (TABLE,,T.Ramsoy+,J,NP/A,438,301,1985) Tbl.1
HISTORY    (20020413C)
           (20251214A) SD: Corrections in all Subents.
           ANG1 -> ANG.
ENDBIB              23
COMMON               3          3
EN         ANG        EN-RSL-FW
MEV        ADEG       MEV
  15.0        50.0      0.15
ENDCOMMON            3
ENDSUBENT           30
SUBENT        F0543002   20251214   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  4          7
REACTION   ((66-DY-161(D,T)66-DY-160,PAR,DA)/
           (66-DY-161(D,EL)66-DY-161,,DA))
EN-SEC     (E-EXC,66-DY-160)
SAMPLE     (66-DY-161,ENR=0.90) Self-supporting foil enriched
           to 90% in 161Dy. The target thickness was 1.0 mg/cm2.
HISTORY    (20251214A) SD: SF6=SIG -> DA in REACTION code.
           BIB updated.
ENDBIB               7
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 2          8
E-EXC      DATA
MEV        NO-DIM
       1.38   2.90E-04
       1.81   3.30E-04
       2.10   6.00E-04
       2.33   2.31E-03
       2.49   1.28E-03
       2.91   1.50E-04
       3.15   1.60E-04
        3.6   8.00E-05
ENDDATA             10
ENDSUBENT           22
SUBENT        F0543003   20251214   20260305   20260305       F105
BIB                  4          8
REACTION   ((66-DY-163(D,T)66-DY-162,PAR,DA)/
           (66-DY-163(D,EL)66-DY-163,,DA))
EN-SEC     (E-EXC,66-DY-162)
SAMPLE     (66-DY-163,ENR=0.97) Self-supporting foil enriched to
           97% 163Dy. The target thickness was 1.7 mg/cm2.
HISTORY    (20251214A) SD: BIB updated. SF6=SIG -> DA;
           SF1=Dy-162 -> Dy-163; SF4nominator =Dy-161 -> Dy-162;
           SF4denominator=Dy-162 -> Dy-163 in REACTION code.
ENDBIB               8
NOCOMMON             0          0
DATA                 2          8
E-EXC      DATA
MEV        NO-DIM
       1.57   7.50E-04
       1.79   6.80E-04
       2.14   7.40E-04
       2.31   2.03E-03
       2.49   1.19E-03
       3.02   4.20E-04
       3.20   2.50E-04
       3.66   1.40E-04
ENDDATA             10
ENDSUBENT           23
ENDENTRY             3
